WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.801
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on "Devious Maids"...</i>

00:01.803 --> 00:03.711
Christopher's
moving in here with us,

00:03.747 --> 00:06.208
and Joy's been his housekeeper
for years.

00:06.243 --> 00:08.490
You need help
while you're pregnant.

00:08.492 --> 00:10.626
You can't clean
this big house alone.

00:10.628 --> 00:12.227
Zoila has been
trying to undermine

00:12.229 --> 00:14.062
my relationship with Genevieve.

00:14.064 --> 00:16.064
And I'm counting on you
to help me.

00:16.065 --> 00:20.469
Adrian, this is Deion,
our new son.

00:20.471 --> 00:21.904
Why would you
want to have a kid?

00:21.906 --> 00:24.206
Your house is so quiet.

00:24.208 --> 00:26.408
What if something bad
happened to Blanca

00:26.410 --> 00:29.912
at the Stappords' house
and that's why she was killed?

00:29.914 --> 00:32.648
[Gasps]
Oh, my God. Olivia.

00:32.650 --> 00:34.516
She's also
the first Mrs. Stappord,

00:34.518 --> 00:36.084
and a world-class psycho.

00:36.086 --> 00:37.819
I'm here because
I'm looking to hire a new maid.

00:37.821 --> 00:39.187
Jesse really is
a wonderful maid.

00:39.189 --> 00:40.822
Say no more.
He's got the job.

00:40.824 --> 00:43.425
Olivia, she said
Blanca was murdered.

00:43.427 --> 00:47.062
You think Mr. Michael's ex-wife
murdered Blanca?

00:47.064 --> 00:48.263
If she did, she had help.

00:48.265 --> 00:49.765
I just wanted to let you know

00:49.767 --> 00:51.533
that I'm sending you
the rest of your money.

00:51.535 --> 00:53.936
Everything's working out
just as I planned.

00:53.938 --> 00:56.772
Katy's a witness, and the men
who killed her father

00:56.774 --> 00:58.407
are looking for her.

00:58.409 --> 01:00.375
Violeta?

01:00.377 --> 01:02.577
I want to talk to <i>El Jefe.</i>
I want to make a deal.

01:02.579 --> 01:04.546
I found the little girl
he's been looking for.

01:04.548 --> 01:06.615
How's Ernesto?

01:06.617 --> 01:08.583
He had to go back to México
for a little bit.

01:08.585 --> 01:11.553
You're a great man,
Mr. Spence.

01:11.555 --> 01:14.556
♪

01:16.693 --> 01:20.696
That's weird.
I thought I made more cupcakes.

01:20.698 --> 01:22.898
Where are all the other ones?

01:22.900 --> 01:24.032
I don't know.

01:24.034 --> 01:25.801
You ate them.

01:25.803 --> 01:27.302
What?
I had one cupcake.

01:27.304 --> 01:28.304
Hmm.

01:28.305 --> 01:30.238
Okay, three cupcakes.

01:30.240 --> 01:31.907
[Speaks Spanish]

01:31.909 --> 01:33.809
You better hope we have enough
for Miguel's birthday.

01:33.811 --> 01:35.711
We will.

01:35.713 --> 01:38.413
It was nice of Taylor to let you
throw the party at her house.

01:38.415 --> 01:40.909
Well, she's out of town
with Katy.

01:42.052 --> 01:44.453
Anyway,
thanks for all of your help.

01:44.455 --> 01:46.455
Are you kidding?
I'd do anything for Miguel.

01:46.457 --> 01:48.290
[Sighs] I know.

01:48.292 --> 01:52.394
And, to be honest, it gives me
a chance to spend time with you.

01:52.396 --> 01:54.129
Yes.

01:54.131 --> 01:58.266
Well, uh, it's good
we can still be friends.

01:58.268 --> 02:02.170
Is that what we are now?
Friends?

02:02.172 --> 02:03.905
What else would we be?

02:03.907 --> 02:05.507
I don't know.

02:05.509 --> 02:08.744
It seems like
since Ernesto left town,

02:08.746 --> 02:10.145
we've been getting closer.

02:10.146 --> 02:11.847
You've got frosting
on your face.

02:11.849 --> 02:13.148
You're changing the subject.

02:13.150 --> 02:15.784
No, no. [Chuckles]

02:15.786 --> 02:18.146
You really do have frosting.

02:19.689 --> 02:22.724
♪

02:28.865 --> 02:31.299
[Doorbell rings]

02:31.301 --> 02:34.302
I have to get that.

02:40.043 --> 02:41.877
Ernesto?

02:41.879 --> 02:44.713
<i>Mi amor.</i>

02:44.715 --> 02:46.481
Mm-wah.

02:46.483 --> 02:49.117
[Sighs]
You look so surprised.

02:49.119 --> 02:51.153
I didn't know
you were coming back.

02:51.155 --> 02:53.355
I wasn't gonna miss
Miguel's birthday.

02:53.357 --> 02:55.557
[Chuckles]

02:55.559 --> 02:56.558
Oh.

02:56.560 --> 02:57.993
Spence.

02:57.995 --> 02:59.628
Hi.

02:59.630 --> 03:03.298
I was just, uh,
helping with the party.

03:03.300 --> 03:06.568
That's nice.
But I'm here now.

03:06.570 --> 03:07.869
You're not the only one.

03:07.871 --> 03:09.938
Mmm.

03:15.845 --> 03:18.847
<b>- sync and corrections by Zac -
- www.addic7ed.com -</b>

03:20.000 --> 03:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:27.056 --> 03:28.356
Morning.

03:28.358 --> 03:30.025
What are you doing
in my room, kid?

03:30.027 --> 03:33.495
Being bored, mostly.
What's this thing?

03:33.497 --> 03:35.564
A designer fashion accessory.

03:35.566 --> 03:37.199
Where do you wear it?

03:37.201 --> 03:39.401
Anywhere. To the grocery store,
to the red carpet.

03:39.403 --> 03:41.763
Why am I even
explaining this to you?

03:43.206 --> 03:44.840
[Giggles]

03:44.842 --> 03:46.441
<i>Mira,</i> you can't just
break in here

03:46.443 --> 03:48.276
and start
playing with my stuff.

03:48.278 --> 03:50.545
My career is in the toilet.
I'm in no mood.

03:50.547 --> 03:52.848
Your career?
I thought you were a maid.

03:52.850 --> 03:54.850
I'm a singer.

03:54.852 --> 03:56.518
But my record label
just dumped me.

03:56.520 --> 03:57.752
So you're a bad singer.

03:57.754 --> 04:00.222
You know what?
I'm done with you.

04:00.224 --> 04:01.785
Let's go.
[Giggles]

04:03.092 --> 04:04.292
Mrs. Powell.

04:04.294 --> 04:06.294
Carmen.
Something wrong?

04:06.296 --> 04:09.297
Yeah, I woke up and found
this little creep in my room

04:09.299 --> 04:10.899
playing with
my personal things.

04:10.901 --> 04:13.021
You, uh, have a little something
on your...

04:16.906 --> 04:18.740
Perfect.

04:18.742 --> 04:20.742
Well, thank you for bringing

04:20.744 --> 04:22.944
Deion's behavior
to my attention.

04:22.946 --> 04:24.212
Now you're in for it.

04:24.214 --> 04:25.814
You listen to me, young man.

04:25.816 --> 04:28.650
You need to
get your things together,

04:28.652 --> 04:32.654
because the car is waiting
to take us to Disneyland!

04:32.656 --> 04:34.956
- Whoo-hoo!
- Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

04:34.958 --> 04:36.158
[Laughs] What?

04:36.160 --> 04:37.592
You're supposed to punish him.

04:37.594 --> 04:40.228
Well, I can't very well
punish the child

04:40.230 --> 04:41.763
and <i> then</i> take him
to Disneyland.

04:41.765 --> 04:43.231
It would send a mixed message.

04:43.233 --> 04:46.234
Anyway, Adrian is away
for a golf weekend,

04:46.236 --> 04:47.602
so now is your chance

04:47.604 --> 04:49.604
to get some real cleaning done
around here.

04:49.606 --> 04:50.939
Real cleaning?

04:50.941 --> 04:53.341
Vacuum the sofa,
clean the windows.

04:53.343 --> 04:55.110
Shave your upper lip.

04:59.982 --> 05:01.816
Son of a bitch.

05:01.818 --> 05:05.787
I wanted to talk to you about
something delicate, actually.

05:05.789 --> 05:07.322
Is this about Taylor?

05:07.324 --> 05:09.591
No. Olivia.

05:09.593 --> 05:11.793
I don't want to spread rumors,
but I ran into her,

05:11.795 --> 05:13.295
and she said that you two
are seeing each other.

05:13.297 --> 05:14.796
Oh.

05:14.798 --> 05:16.998
I know.
She's delusional, right?

05:17.000 --> 05:18.667
Just when you think she can't
get any more bananas...

05:18.669 --> 05:19.935
We're seeing each other.

05:19.937 --> 05:21.036
Hmm?

05:21.038 --> 05:22.671
She's not delusional.

05:22.673 --> 05:25.340
We've sort of...
reconnected.

05:25.342 --> 05:27.542
Well, forgive me
for being blunt,

05:27.544 --> 05:29.044
but what the hell
are you thinking?

05:29.046 --> 05:31.146
- I'm sorry?
- Olivia is deranged.

05:31.148 --> 05:33.715
Don't you remember all those
crazy stunts she used to pull?

05:33.717 --> 05:35.350
She's...
[Sighs]

05:35.352 --> 05:36.952
She's different now.

05:36.954 --> 05:38.386
How is she different?

05:38.388 --> 05:40.121
This is none of your business.

05:40.123 --> 05:43.124
You came to me, remember?

05:43.126 --> 05:44.492
You told me Taylor
was having an affair,

05:44.494 --> 05:46.328
but now you're the one
who's cheating?

05:46.330 --> 05:48.730
- Taylor did have an affair.
- So what is this, retaliation?

05:48.732 --> 05:51.166
I just don't understand why you
would ever go back to Olivia.

05:51.168 --> 05:53.001
Well, good thing I don't have to
explain myself to you.

05:53.003 --> 05:54.769
Michael. Michael, wait.

05:56.239 --> 05:58.073
[Sighs]

05:58.075 --> 06:01.042
I think Olivia might have been
involved in Blanca's death.

06:01.044 --> 06:03.011
You don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

06:03.013 --> 06:04.846
Maybe she hired someone?
I don't know.

06:04.848 --> 06:06.548
But she's up to something.

06:06.550 --> 06:10.986
Someday, you're gonna
regret saying that.

06:10.988 --> 06:14.022
♪

06:14.024 --> 06:15.423
[Door slams]

06:15.425 --> 06:18.360
Wow.
That's quite a breakfast.

06:18.362 --> 06:19.995
So unhealthy,
but the baby's craving it,

06:19.997 --> 06:21.663
and I can't say no to the baby.

06:21.665 --> 06:25.233
Well, I hate to interrupt
while you're feeding,

06:25.235 --> 06:28.169
but I wanted to ask you
a favor.

06:28.171 --> 06:29.771
Shoot.

06:29.773 --> 06:33.441
Could I maybe...
borrow $100?

06:33.443 --> 06:35.443
[Coughs]

06:35.445 --> 06:38.280
That's a lot of money to ask of
someone you hardly know.

06:38.282 --> 06:41.516
I'm sorry. It's just [Sighs]
I'm in such a pickle.

06:41.518 --> 06:43.752
My paycheck
from Dr. Neff bounced.

06:43.754 --> 06:45.120
Really?

06:45.122 --> 06:48.556
It happens from time to time.

06:48.558 --> 06:51.192
The truth is...
Uh, no, I shouldn't gossip.

06:51.194 --> 06:52.761
Mnh-mnh.

06:52.763 --> 06:54.629
You need 100 bucks,
I need 100 bucks worth of dirt.

06:55.073 --> 06:59.980
[Sighs] Well, Dr. Neff isn't
exactly good with money.

07:00.070 --> 07:02.070
He pays alimony
to six ex-wives,

07:02.072 --> 07:04.439
and he's made
some terrible investments.

07:04.441 --> 07:06.174
So, he's...

07:07.777 --> 07:09.644
broke?

07:09.646 --> 07:12.447
Don't worry. He'll figure
something out. [Door opens]

07:12.449 --> 07:14.449
Zoila!
[Door closes]

07:14.451 --> 07:15.583
Excuse me.

07:15.585 --> 07:17.118
Oh, good.

07:17.120 --> 07:18.820
Will you take these up
to the bedroom, please?

07:18.822 --> 07:20.422
What is all this?

07:20.424 --> 07:22.625
I mentioned to Genevieve that
I needed some new clothes,

07:22.626 --> 07:25.226
so she surprised me
with a whole new wardrobe.

07:25.228 --> 07:28.229
[Sighs]
Doesn't he look fantastic?

07:28.231 --> 07:30.398
I think we bought out
all of Rodeo Drive.

07:30.400 --> 07:33.501
So, you just let Genevieve pay
for everything?

07:33.503 --> 07:35.737
She insisted.

07:35.739 --> 07:38.940
Looks like I landed myself
a sweet little sugar mama.

07:38.942 --> 07:41.142
[Chuckles]

07:41.144 --> 07:43.445
♪

07:43.447 --> 07:46.648
So, while Mrs. Taylor's
out of town with Katy,

07:46.650 --> 07:48.750
I've been busy getting ready
for Miguel's party.

07:48.752 --> 07:51.019
- She took Katy?
- Mm-hmm.

07:51.021 --> 07:52.954
Did they say
when they will be back?

07:52.956 --> 07:54.356
Next week.

07:54.358 --> 07:56.157
[Chuckles] Why do you care?

07:56.159 --> 07:58.360
Oh, just...

07:58.362 --> 08:00.995
want to know how long
I'll have you to myself.

08:00.997 --> 08:03.431
Aww. That's nice.

08:03.433 --> 08:06.167
So, what can I do to help you
with Miguel's party.

08:06.169 --> 08:08.203
Nothing. We did a lot
while you were gone.

08:08.205 --> 08:09.771
You and Spence.

08:09.773 --> 08:12.640
He's trying to weasel his way
back into your life.

08:12.642 --> 08:15.310
He's just helping out with the
party because he loves Miguel.

08:15.312 --> 08:17.212
I don't like you spending
so much time with him.

08:17.214 --> 08:19.948
Well, I don't like you disappearing
to México for three weeks.

08:19.950 --> 08:23.017
Yeah.

08:23.019 --> 08:27.021
Rosita, I-I don't
want to be jealous.

08:27.023 --> 08:29.324
Just tell me there's
nothing there, and I'll drop it.

08:29.326 --> 08:31.526
There's nothing there.

08:31.528 --> 08:33.962
Good.

08:33.964 --> 08:35.163
Now let's order dessert.

08:35.164 --> 08:36.297
[Sighs]

08:38.200 --> 08:40.635
Uh, Marisol,
Olivia isn't home right now.

08:40.636 --> 08:44.472
Well, I came to see you.
To see how things are going.

08:44.474 --> 08:46.474
She's... she's pretty easy
to work for.

08:46.476 --> 08:48.476
Good.

08:48.478 --> 08:51.079
Does she get many visitors?

08:51.081 --> 08:52.347
A few.

08:52.349 --> 08:55.350
Anyone worth mentioning?

08:55.352 --> 08:56.551
What is this?

08:56.553 --> 08:58.653
What is what?

08:58.655 --> 09:00.155
You're snooping.

09:00.157 --> 09:04.058
I am not. We are just
having a casual conversation.

09:04.060 --> 09:06.494
But if you saw her
do anything suspicious,

09:06.496 --> 09:07.862
you would tell me, right?

09:07.864 --> 09:10.198
Oh, my God, you are snooping.

09:10.200 --> 09:12.600
Fine, I'm snooping.
Happy?

09:12.602 --> 09:14.235
You just can't help yourself,
can you?

09:14.237 --> 09:16.671
I'm just trying to figure out
who killed my friend Blanca.

09:16.673 --> 09:18.406
Look, it was bad enough
when you accused me.

09:18.408 --> 09:19.607
Now you think Olivia did it?

09:19.609 --> 09:22.610
I'm not sure!
That's why I'm snooping.

09:22.612 --> 09:24.846
[Clears throat] Well,
let me save you the trouble.

09:24.848 --> 09:26.714
Olivia didn't kill anyone.

09:26.716 --> 09:29.417
You barely know her.
Why are you defending her?

09:29.419 --> 09:31.419
Because she has cancer.

09:31.421 --> 09:33.755
[Gasps] What?

09:33.757 --> 09:36.391
Yeah.
She didn't kill your friend.

09:36.393 --> 09:39.227
She's been too busy
fighting for her own life.

09:39.229 --> 09:40.228
♪

09:43.027 --> 09:46.513
<i>Santo dios.</i>
She's got the cancer?

09:46.548 --> 09:48.078
Jesse says it's advanced.

09:48.080 --> 09:50.180
Olivia's been
going to chemo for months.

09:50.182 --> 09:52.950
Ouch! You really stepped in it
with him, didn't you?

09:52.952 --> 09:56.353
Yeah. Trying to pin a murder on
a woman with cancer? That's low.

09:56.355 --> 09:58.088
- Yeah, I'm aware.
- Like, you're going to hell.

09:58.090 --> 09:59.890
Thank you, Carmen.

09:59.892 --> 10:01.892
But the truth is,
just because she has cancer

10:01.894 --> 10:04.194
doesn't mean she's suddenly
a good person.

10:04.196 --> 10:07.197
I do feel bad for her,
even if she is crazy.

10:07.199 --> 10:09.867
Yeah. Cancer's the worst.
Nobody deserves that.

10:09.869 --> 10:12.369
Well, it sure makes me think.

10:12.371 --> 10:13.971
That life is too short?

10:13.973 --> 10:16.406
No, that she must be
milking this cancer

10:16.408 --> 10:17.808
for everything it's worth.

10:17.810 --> 10:19.643
Marisol, that's horrible.

10:19.645 --> 10:21.111
Go on.

10:21.113 --> 10:22.779
This is probably
how she lured him back.

10:22.781 --> 10:24.548
Michael's always had
a soft spot for Olivia

10:24.550 --> 10:26.750
- when she's in distress.
- So what?

10:26.752 --> 10:28.151
If I got cancer, I'd milk it.

10:28.153 --> 10:29.887
You milk it
when you break a fingernail.

10:29.889 --> 10:31.488
You know what, that reminds me.
I need a manicure.

10:31.490 --> 10:32.990
Can someone
pay for my lunch today?

10:32.992 --> 10:34.892
No. No. No.

10:34.894 --> 10:37.261
You should ask Genevieve. She's
handing out money left and right.

10:37.263 --> 10:39.463
- What?
- Oh, yeah.

10:39.465 --> 10:42.099
Her boyfriend's broke,
he's using her as an ATM,

10:42.101 --> 10:43.500
but she has no idea.

10:43.502 --> 10:44.935
Then you've got to tell her.

10:44.937 --> 10:46.470
Oh, no.
I've learned my lesson.

10:46.472 --> 10:48.005
I am not getting in the middle.

10:48.007 --> 10:49.806
Besides,
they're not that serious.

10:49.808 --> 10:52.910
Well, if I was dating a leech,
I would want someone to tell me.

10:52.912 --> 10:55.312
- What's a leech?
- Someone who takes and takes

10:55.314 --> 10:57.114
and never gives
anything in return.

10:57.116 --> 10:58.582
Oh, like Carmen.

10:59.751 --> 11:01.585
Oh, is this your purse?

11:04.422 --> 11:06.023
Two for lunch, please.

11:06.025 --> 11:07.791
[Chuckles]
There's a 45-minute wait.

11:07.793 --> 11:09.192
45 minutes?

11:09.194 --> 11:11.161
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh, dear.

11:11.163 --> 11:15.999
I just feel so weak
after my chemo treatment.

11:16.001 --> 11:18.001
See, I have cancer.

11:21.539 --> 11:24.308
I believe
something just opened up.

11:27.378 --> 11:29.413
[Indistinct conversations]

11:31.382 --> 11:34.618
[Sighs]

11:34.620 --> 11:36.620
I am sorry I'm late.

11:36.622 --> 11:37.955
I'm just glad you're here.

11:37.957 --> 11:39.189
How you feeling?

11:39.191 --> 11:40.958
You're looking at my hair.

11:40.960 --> 11:43.961
I'm sorry.
[Sighs]

11:43.963 --> 11:47.698
I wasn't expecting...
Did the chemo...?

11:47.700 --> 11:49.533
No, no.
I shaved it off myself.

11:49.535 --> 11:51.535
I figured I'd take matters
into my own hands

11:51.537 --> 11:53.370
before it all falls out.

11:53.372 --> 11:56.173
What do you think?

11:56.175 --> 12:00.010
I think...
you look beautiful.

12:00.012 --> 12:03.513
You're so sweet.

12:03.515 --> 12:07.718
So [Clears throat]
what can we get you to eat?

12:07.720 --> 12:10.187
[Chuckles]

12:10.189 --> 12:12.823
Olivia? What's wrong?

12:12.825 --> 12:16.426
No. I don't want to
ruin our time together.

12:16.428 --> 12:18.228
I don't see you nearly enough.

12:18.230 --> 12:20.797
Tell me.
I'm here for you.

12:24.002 --> 12:26.403
The treatment isn't working.

12:26.405 --> 12:28.405
The doctors say
I don't have much time.

12:28.407 --> 12:30.374
Oh, my God.

12:31.743 --> 12:34.063
Is there anything I can do?

12:35.413 --> 12:38.248
[Voice breaking]
Well, there is one thing.

12:39.517 --> 12:41.852
Move in with me.

12:43.187 --> 12:44.588
Oh.

12:44.590 --> 12:46.423
You're the only man
I've ever loved,

12:46.425 --> 12:48.058
and I don't want to die alone.

12:52.964 --> 12:55.198
Of course I'll move in.

12:55.200 --> 12:59.503
Oh, Michael.
That's all I've ever wanted.

13:03.307 --> 13:06.743
We have to
spend less time together.

13:06.745 --> 13:08.945
And yet here you are
in my apartment.

13:08.947 --> 13:12.215
I mean it. Ernesto thinks
you're trying to win me back.

13:12.217 --> 13:14.418
Well, I guess he's not as dumb
as I thought he was.

13:14.420 --> 13:15.752
- Spence.
- What?

13:15.754 --> 13:17.754
I love you,
and I am not just gonna

13:17.756 --> 13:19.156
sit around on the sidelines
anymore.

13:19.158 --> 13:21.591
<i>Ay!</i>
You know I'm with Ernesto.

13:21.593 --> 13:23.593
Why are you saying
these things?

13:23.595 --> 13:25.796
Because you don't want me
to give up.

13:25.798 --> 13:27.798
The other night,
when I kissed you,

13:27.800 --> 13:29.132
you kissed me back.

13:30.601 --> 13:33.003
I don't think you should come
to Miguel's party.

13:33.005 --> 13:34.438
What? Why not?

13:34.440 --> 13:36.440
Because Ernesto's going, too,

13:36.442 --> 13:38.408
and I don't want it
to be complicated.

13:38.410 --> 13:41.611
I'm sorry. I told Miguel
I'd be there. I'm going.

13:41.613 --> 13:43.480
Ernesto won't like it.

13:43.482 --> 13:45.215
Well, that will be
an added bonus.

13:48.453 --> 13:50.420
So, let me get this straight.

13:50.422 --> 13:52.789
You looked <i> El Jefe</i> in the eyes,
and you told him you wanted out?

13:52.791 --> 13:56.359
He says I'm free to walk away
as long as he gets the girl.

13:57.310 --> 14:02.299
Well, that's a very happy ending
for you and your family.

14:02.301 --> 14:05.001
Not so happy
for little Violeta.

14:05.003 --> 14:06.803
Katy.

14:06.805 --> 14:09.339
The people who adopted her,
they changed her name to Katy.

14:09.341 --> 14:11.007
So, when do we take her?

14:11.009 --> 14:12.509
I don't know.
The mother took her out of town.

14:12.511 --> 14:14.344
You trying to stall, Ernesto?

14:14.346 --> 14:17.647
She's not there. I'll take you.
You can see for yourself.

14:17.649 --> 14:19.649
That's good.

14:19.651 --> 14:23.487
We can check out the house,
make a plan.

14:23.489 --> 14:24.688
How do we get in?

14:26.524 --> 14:29.960
It won't be hard.
My wife works there.

14:29.962 --> 14:32.362
[Sniffs]
Your wife has seen me before.

14:32.364 --> 14:33.930
Won't she recognize me?

14:36.534 --> 14:39.369
I got an idea.

14:39.371 --> 14:44.074
Oh, Carmen!
Disneyland was an absolute hoot.

14:44.076 --> 14:46.510
I went on Splash Mountain
four times.

14:46.512 --> 14:50.514
And I tried this delightful
concoction called a corn dog.

14:50.516 --> 14:52.516
[Laughs]
You should have been there.

14:52.518 --> 14:53.917
Oh, I wasn't invited.

14:53.919 --> 14:55.886
Because I was here
cleaning your toilet.

14:55.888 --> 14:58.522
You're just mad because
we're rich and you're not.

14:58.524 --> 15:00.924
Sweetheart, it's not polite

15:00.926 --> 15:02.559
to discuss
how much money you have.

15:02.561 --> 15:04.194
Now, go wash up.

15:04.196 --> 15:05.695
We'll order in from Spago

15:05.697 --> 15:07.697
and project "Frozen" on the wall
of the east terrace.

15:07.699 --> 15:09.099
Yes!

15:09.101 --> 15:11.034
[Scoffs]

15:11.036 --> 15:12.869
Oh.

15:12.871 --> 15:16.106
You seem to be in
a more sour mood than usual.

15:16.108 --> 15:17.440
It's none of my business,

15:17.442 --> 15:19.342
but you're turning that kid
into a brat.

15:19.344 --> 15:22.412
That is a bit extreme.

15:22.414 --> 15:24.447
He comes in my room.
He draws on my face.

15:24.449 --> 15:25.916
He goes through my things.

15:25.918 --> 15:27.551
- Normal child's play.
- No!

15:27.553 --> 15:29.119
He needs a firm hand.

15:29.121 --> 15:32.756
Well, I don't want
Deion to grow up without

15:32.758 --> 15:36.593
a healthy fear of authority.

15:36.595 --> 15:38.361
Perhaps he could use
a little discipline.

15:38.363 --> 15:41.097
Good.
I'm glad you agree.

15:41.099 --> 15:43.066
You'll take care of that, then?

15:43.068 --> 15:45.101
Take care of what?

15:45.103 --> 15:46.736
Discipline...
From now on,

15:46.738 --> 15:49.272
punishing Deion
will be part of your job.

15:49.274 --> 15:50.640
Why do I have to do it?

15:50.642 --> 15:53.343
[Laughs]
I don't care if he hates you.

15:55.713 --> 15:58.215
Hey, Joy, would you bring in

15:58.217 --> 16:00.817
the rest of the groceries
from the car?

16:00.819 --> 16:03.420
Shh!
You did not just shush me.

16:03.422 --> 16:05.822
Oh, sorry.
But you're ruining the moment.

16:05.824 --> 16:08.258
Dr. Neff is proposing
to Mrs. Delatour.

16:08.260 --> 16:10.894
Oh, my God.

16:10.896 --> 16:12.162
Excuse me.

16:12.164 --> 16:14.798
I-I can't...
Get out of my way.

16:14.800 --> 16:17.434
And, so,
I may have fixed your kidney,

16:17.436 --> 16:21.271
but you have fixed my heart.

16:21.273 --> 16:25.575
Genevieve, will you marry me?

16:25.577 --> 16:27.978
[Groans]

16:27.980 --> 16:29.946
Zoila?
What's the matter?

16:31.282 --> 16:33.917
I think I just went into labor!

16:33.919 --> 16:34.951
[Groans]

16:36.120 --> 16:38.255
[Groans]

16:40.208 --> 16:41.091
Hi, Miss Rice.

16:41.092 --> 16:44.469
Oh! Jesse, I didn't
realize you were here.

16:44.504 --> 16:46.928
Have you eaten?
Can I make you anything?

16:46.930 --> 16:48.930
No, thanks.
I just had some broth.

16:48.932 --> 16:51.032
That's all I can keep down.

16:51.034 --> 16:52.667
[Sighs]

16:52.669 --> 16:54.102
I know
what you're going through.

16:54.104 --> 16:56.705
My... my father
had lung cancer.

16:56.707 --> 16:58.139
He passed away a few years ago.

16:58.141 --> 17:00.141
- Oh, dear.
- Yeah.

17:00.143 --> 17:03.845
If you don't mind me asking,
what kind of cancer do you have?

17:03.847 --> 17:07.281
Well, at this point,
it's all over.

17:07.284 --> 17:09.284
You know how it spreads.

17:09.286 --> 17:12.954
Anyway, I have good news.
My ex-husband is moving in.

17:12.955 --> 17:14.289
Ah, great.

17:14.290 --> 17:16.290
Yes. Please make up
the guest room.

17:16.292 --> 17:18.126
That's where
he'll be staying...

17:18.127 --> 17:19.994
for now.

17:20.196 --> 17:23.198
♪

17:35.545 --> 17:37.946
Dr. Neff, thank you so much
for driving,

17:37.948 --> 17:39.514
but you don't have to stay.

17:39.516 --> 17:42.351
Zoila, we're about to experience
the miracle of birth.

17:42.353 --> 17:45.087
- I wouldn't dream of leaving.
- You're so sweet.

17:45.089 --> 17:47.356
But I need a moment alone
with Genevieve. Lady stuff.

17:47.358 --> 17:49.558
I'm a doctor. You can say
anything in front of me.

17:50.960 --> 17:53.195
[Groans loudly]

17:53.197 --> 17:54.463
It hurts so bad.

17:54.465 --> 17:56.298
Can you let someone know
I'm here, please?

17:56.300 --> 17:58.066
I'll inform the nurses.

17:58.068 --> 17:59.401
Don't forget to breathe.

17:59.403 --> 18:00.569
[Inhales deeply,
Lamaze breathing]

18:00.571 --> 18:02.137
Knock it off.
I'm not in labor.

18:02.139 --> 18:03.772
You're not?

18:03.774 --> 18:06.308
No. I had to stop the proposal,
and I-I panicked.

18:06.310 --> 18:07.643
Why would you do that?

18:07.645 --> 18:08.877
'Cause I needed to
tell you something

18:08.879 --> 18:10.078
before you got engaged.

18:10.080 --> 18:11.647
Dr. Neff is broke.

18:11.649 --> 18:14.416
That's ridiculous.
He's a world-renowned surgeon.

18:14.418 --> 18:15.817
I know,
but he's in serious debt.

18:15.819 --> 18:17.252
Alimony, bad investments,

18:17.254 --> 18:19.821
bills up to his
big bushy eyebrows.

18:19.823 --> 18:21.456
Are you certain?

18:21.458 --> 18:23.058
Joy told me.

18:23.060 --> 18:24.660
Why else would he be in
such a hurry to get married?

18:24.662 --> 18:28.096
Because he loves me
with every fiber of his being.

18:28.098 --> 18:29.998
There's no way he's using me
for my money.

18:30.000 --> 18:32.234
[Breathing deeply]
Genevieve, I need your wallet.

18:32.236 --> 18:34.169
I'm sorry?

18:34.171 --> 18:36.872
If I tip the orderly,
I can get Zoila a private room.

18:42.745 --> 18:45.981
What would I do without you?

18:45.983 --> 18:49.918
♪

19:00.663 --> 19:03.432
- Aah!
- Yes.

19:03.434 --> 19:05.534
Deion, hey, get over here.
Now.

19:05.536 --> 19:08.170
- You can't tell me what to do.
- Oh, yes, I can.

19:08.172 --> 19:10.639
Mrs. Powell says
I'm in charge of punishing you.

19:10.641 --> 19:12.974
Oh.
Are you gonna spank me?

19:12.976 --> 19:15.610
<i>Oh, no, niño.</i>

19:15.612 --> 19:18.480
It's gonna be
way worse than that.

19:18.482 --> 19:21.016
[Grunting]

19:22.719 --> 19:24.986
Deion?!

19:24.988 --> 19:26.988
What on earth are you doing?

19:26.990 --> 19:29.057
Why are you
on your hands and knees?

19:29.059 --> 19:31.226
Bitch made me do her chores.

19:31.228 --> 19:34.129
[Gasps]
A Powell never says that word.

19:34.131 --> 19:35.197
"Bitch"?

19:35.199 --> 19:37.032
No. "Chores."

19:37.034 --> 19:38.700
Carmen!

19:40.336 --> 19:45.173
Did you make my little boy
do your housework?

19:45.175 --> 19:47.242
I sure did.

19:47.244 --> 19:50.245
The housework
that I pay you to do.

19:50.247 --> 19:52.347
You told me to be
the firm hand.

19:52.349 --> 19:56.485
Well, this is unacceptable.
I'm docking your pay.

19:56.487 --> 19:59.087
- You can't do that.
- Oh, yes, I can.

19:59.089 --> 20:01.022
I'm subtracting a substantial
yet arbitrary amount of money

20:01.024 --> 20:02.424
from your check.

20:02.426 --> 20:04.326
So, you can punish me
and not your kid?

20:04.328 --> 20:07.729
And now I'm doubling the amount
for talking back to me.

20:12.001 --> 20:14.836
Knock, knock.
Hello, Rosie.

20:14.838 --> 20:18.673
Mr. Michael, I didn't know
you'd be coming over today.

20:18.675 --> 20:20.275
Well, I'm checking
out of the hotel tomorrow.

20:20.277 --> 20:22.944
I just needed to pick up
a few things.

20:22.946 --> 20:24.513
Oh, uh, Rosie,
this is Olivia Rice.

20:24.515 --> 20:28.016
Oh, yes.
I have... heard about you.

20:28.018 --> 20:31.086
I'd shake your hand,
but I have cancer.

20:32.388 --> 20:34.089
I'll just be a few minutes.

20:36.092 --> 20:40.929
So, does Taylor always keep
the house this... festive?

20:40.931 --> 20:44.132
Oh, it's, uh, for my
little boy's birthday party.

20:44.134 --> 20:46.301
She was nice enough
to let us have it here.

20:46.303 --> 20:49.938
You know, I used to live here
with Michael.

20:49.940 --> 20:53.141
I designed the entire house.

20:53.143 --> 20:56.144
From the Marquina marble
countertops to the...

20:56.146 --> 20:58.146
Oh, my God.

20:58.148 --> 21:00.782
Where's the coffee table?

21:00.784 --> 21:02.217
It's right there.

21:04.320 --> 21:07.956
That mass-produced
piece of junk

21:07.958 --> 21:10.959
is most certainly not
my custom table.

21:10.961 --> 21:14.162
Well, it's been there since
I started working here.

21:14.164 --> 21:17.666
Oh, no.
My Italian sofa.

21:17.668 --> 21:19.167
These slipcovers
have been laundered.

21:19.169 --> 21:22.604
The label states clearly
"dry-clean only."

21:22.606 --> 21:26.007
Blanca must have done that.
I've never touched those.

21:26.009 --> 21:27.776
Oh, for God's sake.

21:27.778 --> 21:30.278
If the cancer wasn't killing me,
this would.

21:30.280 --> 21:32.414
It looks nice to me.

21:32.416 --> 21:35.417
Well, that's why
I'm the designer

21:35.419 --> 21:36.985
and you're the maid.

21:39.689 --> 21:41.323
So, remember when you said
to let you know

21:41.325 --> 21:43.158
if Olivia did anything
suspicious?

21:43.160 --> 21:45.360
Oh, my God. Yes. Do you think
she's up to something?

21:45.362 --> 21:48.663
Yep. Get this.
I found a burger wrapper.

21:48.665 --> 21:52.033
Not exactly the smoking gun
I was hoping for.

21:52.035 --> 21:54.035
Well, except, I remember
when my dad was in chemo,

21:54.037 --> 21:56.037
he did not have an appetite.

21:56.039 --> 21:57.806
So then I started looking
through her house.

21:57.808 --> 21:59.608
You what?
I pulled open some drawers.

21:59.610 --> 22:01.343
I went through
her medicine cabinet.

22:01.345 --> 22:04.112
Wha... Am I hearing this right?
Were you snooping?

22:04.114 --> 22:05.714
Do you want to bust my balls,

22:05.716 --> 22:07.015
or do you
want to know what I found?

22:07.017 --> 22:08.683
All right, tell me.

22:08.685 --> 22:12.954
So, Olivia doesn't have a single
medication to treat cancer,

22:12.956 --> 22:15.156
but she does have
a lot of ipecac syrup.

22:15.158 --> 22:18.360
What kind of cancer patient
would want to induce vomiting?

22:18.362 --> 22:22.097
The kind that would also be
visiting this website.

22:22.098 --> 22:24.199
_

22:24.200 --> 22:25.634
You got to be kidding me.

22:25.636 --> 22:28.503
Olivia's sick, all right,
just not with cancer.

22:28.505 --> 22:29.738
♪

22:33.391 --> 22:35.191
[Children playing]

22:35.293 --> 22:36.093
♪

22:39.430 --> 22:42.265
Hey.
Happy birthday, buddy.

22:42.267 --> 22:43.159
Oh, hey, Spence.

22:43.160 --> 22:45.501
I heard a rumor someone
wanted some socks.

22:45.503 --> 22:48.571
He's just teasing you, <i>papito.</i>

22:48.573 --> 22:49.839
It's a PlayStation.

22:49.841 --> 22:52.508
Thank you, Spence!
Best gift ever!

22:52.510 --> 22:55.177
Did you hear that?
Best gift ever.

22:55.179 --> 22:58.147
Just what he needs, to spend
more time playing video games.

22:58.149 --> 23:02.351
Okay, you both got big ones.
Now put them away.

23:02.353 --> 23:04.020
Today's about Miguel, hmm?

23:04.022 --> 23:05.121
[Doorbell rings]

23:05.123 --> 23:06.155
I'll get it.

23:10.260 --> 23:11.460
[Snorts]

23:11.462 --> 23:13.863
I hate you so much right now.

23:13.865 --> 23:16.599
Hector, you look ridiculous.
[Chuckles]

23:16.601 --> 23:18.000
Just be cool.

23:20.437 --> 23:21.971
Who is this?

23:21.973 --> 23:24.774
I hired a clown for
Miguel's party as a surprise.

23:24.776 --> 23:27.977
Oh, that's so sweet.

23:27.979 --> 23:29.312
What is your name?

23:29.314 --> 23:30.980
Machete.

23:30.982 --> 23:34.150
- Machete the clown?
- Oh.

23:34.152 --> 23:35.685
That's terrifying.

23:35.687 --> 23:38.154
He's joking.
His name is Bobo.

23:38.156 --> 23:41.991
Come meet the birthday boy,
Bobo.

23:43.493 --> 23:46.128
[Chuckles]

23:46.130 --> 23:48.731
Is it just me or is there
something off about that clown?

23:48.733 --> 23:51.367
Mm, don't be jealous just
because Ernesto thought about it

23:51.369 --> 23:53.002
and not you.

23:53.004 --> 23:56.038
Now come help me
with the pizzas.

24:00.410 --> 24:02.845
Yeah, she's faking.

24:02.847 --> 24:04.580
Michael, I am so sorry.
[Knock on door]

24:04.582 --> 24:06.148
I just thought you should know.

24:06.150 --> 24:08.050
If Olivia's capable of
this kind of deception,

24:08.052 --> 24:11.253
she's capable of anything.

24:11.255 --> 24:12.488
Of course. Good luck.

24:12.490 --> 24:13.756
I need to talk to you.

24:13.758 --> 24:15.391
You're not going to
believe this.

24:15.393 --> 24:18.361
Jesse found out that Olivia
is faking her cancer.

24:18.363 --> 24:20.363
Big deal.
I got real problems.

24:20.365 --> 24:22.565
Evelyn Powell asked me
to punish that kid of hers,

24:22.567 --> 24:25.000
and now she's punishing me
for punishing him.

24:25.002 --> 24:27.269
She's the employer.

24:27.271 --> 24:29.038
I'm not sure
what you want me to do.

24:29.040 --> 24:30.439
I want you to fix it.

24:30.441 --> 24:32.274
You stuck me with that <i>bruja</i>,

24:32.276 --> 24:34.437
and I am working really hard
for her.

24:35.011 --> 24:37.279
Fine. Not that hard.
But I'm working.

24:37.281 --> 24:38.914
I just don't get why

24:38.916 --> 24:41.016
she can't discipline
her own stupid kid.

24:41.018 --> 24:42.785
Sweetie,
I know you hate kids...

24:42.787 --> 24:44.787
I don't hate kids.

24:44.789 --> 24:46.922
I just don't have room for them
in my life.

24:46.924 --> 24:50.126
Okay, well,
some people adore them.

24:50.128 --> 24:52.128
And even though she may not seem
like the type,

24:52.130 --> 24:53.570
Evelyn is one of those people.

24:55.065 --> 24:57.066
She ever tell you
about Barrett?

24:57.068 --> 24:58.601
Her son who died?

24:58.603 --> 25:00.770
Yeah. What has that
got to do with this?

25:00.772 --> 25:05.207
Maybe she doesn't want to yell
at Deion because this time,

25:05.209 --> 25:07.276
she's making every second
count.

25:10.046 --> 25:11.647
You're faking cancer?!

25:11.649 --> 25:13.149
What? No!

25:13.151 --> 25:14.950
Don't try and deny it.
I talked to Marisol.

25:14.952 --> 25:16.652
She has proof.
That's absurd.

25:16.654 --> 25:18.487
How would Marisol
know anything?

25:18.489 --> 25:20.730
I cannot believe that you
did this.

25:22.592 --> 25:24.794
All right.

25:25.962 --> 25:28.631
Maybe I did make up a little fib
about having cancer,

25:28.633 --> 25:30.833
but it just shows you
how much I love you, Michael.

25:30.835 --> 25:32.635
I-I shaved my head
for you.

25:32.637 --> 25:34.937
Oh, my God. Now, come on.
Let's get you unpacked.

25:34.939 --> 25:38.007
I'm not moving in with you.
You need serious help.

25:38.009 --> 25:41.143
And if I get help,
then you'll move in with me?

25:41.145 --> 25:44.146
No! Get this through your sick,
twisted brain!

25:44.148 --> 25:47.316
I don't love you, and I'll never
come back to you.

25:47.318 --> 25:50.419
Do you understand me?
Never!

25:53.657 --> 25:56.025
[Door opens, slams]

25:56.027 --> 25:59.862
Bobo, can you make
balloon animals?

25:59.864 --> 26:02.765
Come on, man.
You're a clown.

26:02.767 --> 26:03.579
[Sighs]

26:07.343 --> 26:10.277
I want a monkey.
That's my favorite.

26:13.648 --> 26:16.884
Here.
It's a snake.

26:17.986 --> 26:21.822
Okay, everyone,
time to light the candles.

26:21.824 --> 26:23.958
[Cheering] <i>Vamos, chiquitos.</i>

26:25.961 --> 26:27.695
[Speaks Spanish]

26:27.697 --> 26:28.929
[Laughs]

26:28.931 --> 26:30.598
[Speaking Spanish]

26:30.600 --> 26:33.500
♪

26:41.109 --> 26:42.142
Hmm.

26:44.679 --> 26:46.080
[Camera shutter clicking]

26:50.619 --> 26:51.886
What are you doing?

26:51.888 --> 26:55.055
Uh... was looking
for the bathroom.

26:55.057 --> 26:56.523
Were you taking pictures?

26:56.525 --> 26:58.559
Who, me?

26:58.561 --> 27:00.227
Show me your phone.

27:00.229 --> 27:02.630
Or what?

27:05.500 --> 27:07.501
[Singing in Spanish]

27:12.474 --> 27:14.074
Hey, hey!
Give it to me!

27:14.076 --> 27:15.709
Hey, give me that,
you son of a bitch!

27:15.711 --> 27:18.078
Let go of me!
What the hell are you doing?

27:18.080 --> 27:20.748
Aah, he's trying to
take my phone!

27:20.750 --> 27:22.750
[Grunting]
Stop! No!

27:22.752 --> 27:24.752
[Gasps, screams]

27:24.754 --> 27:27.488
[Indistinct shouting]

27:29.524 --> 27:30.824
[Gasps]

27:30.826 --> 27:34.361
[Groans]

27:34.363 --> 27:38.198
♪

27:40.335 --> 27:43.003
[All murmuring]

27:50.913 --> 27:52.527
Hello, beautiful.

27:52.562 --> 27:55.302
Christopher.
What's this?

27:55.337 --> 27:58.095
Well, my romantic proposal
was interrupted.

27:58.130 --> 27:59.621
Yes.

27:59.688 --> 28:02.856
It's such a shame about
Zoila's false labor pains.

28:02.858 --> 28:06.493
Anyway...

28:06.495 --> 28:08.662
I never got an answer
to my question.

28:08.664 --> 28:11.498
Now, I would get down
on my knee again,

28:11.500 --> 28:13.967
but my arthritis won't permit it
twice in the same week.

28:13.969 --> 28:16.804
[Chuckles] Christopher, wait.

28:16.806 --> 28:21.008
Before you propose again,
I need to ask you something.

28:21.010 --> 28:24.211
Are you...

28:24.213 --> 28:26.346
poor?

28:26.348 --> 28:27.681
What?

28:27.683 --> 28:29.683
Because if you are,
you can tell me.

28:29.685 --> 28:31.885
I'll love you just as much.

28:31.887 --> 28:34.154
Well, nearly as much.

28:34.156 --> 28:35.823
Genevieve, I'm not poor.

28:35.825 --> 28:38.659
In fact, I just made
a substantial donation

28:38.661 --> 28:39.893
to the hospital.

28:39.895 --> 28:42.029
They're naming
the new wing after me.

28:42.031 --> 28:43.730
[Sighs]

28:43.732 --> 28:45.933
Now, to make the donation, I had
to transfer some funds around,

28:45.935 --> 28:47.835
and a couple of checks bounced.

28:47.837 --> 28:50.204
I knew there had to be
a simple explanation.

28:50.206 --> 28:53.607
Who told you I was poor?

28:53.609 --> 28:56.810
Oh, it doesn't matter.

28:58.012 --> 29:00.414
It was Zoila, wasn't it?

29:00.416 --> 29:03.884
Why is she so determined
to keep us apart?

29:03.886 --> 29:06.353
I don't think that's true.

29:06.355 --> 29:09.189
Why else would she be spreading
vicious lies about me?

29:09.191 --> 29:11.525
She thought
she was protecting me.

29:11.527 --> 29:14.127
Zoila has had it in for me
from day one.

29:14.129 --> 29:16.449
And I will no longer abide it.

29:17.398 --> 29:18.932
What are you saying?

29:18.934 --> 29:23.103
I want nothing more in the world
than to marry you.

29:23.105 --> 29:27.307
But you are going to have to
make a choice.

29:27.309 --> 29:31.044
It's me or your maid.

29:31.046 --> 29:34.281
♪

29:35.950 --> 29:38.418
Miguel is very upset.

29:38.420 --> 29:39.820
All right, I'll talk to him.

29:39.822 --> 29:43.490
No. Spence,
you ruined his birthday.

29:43.492 --> 29:44.958
You don't understand.

29:44.960 --> 29:47.661
That clown was taking pictures
in Katy's room.

29:47.663 --> 29:49.463
Why would he be doing that?

29:49.465 --> 29:51.131
I don't know, but I kept seeing
Ernesto whisper in his ear.

29:51.133 --> 29:53.467
Enough!

29:53.469 --> 29:58.305
I have been trying to have it
both ways with you and Ernesto,

29:58.307 --> 29:59.907
but no more.

29:59.909 --> 30:01.675
What are you saying?

30:01.677 --> 30:04.945
I can't be friends with you.

30:04.947 --> 30:07.614
Because you love me.

30:07.616 --> 30:11.818
Of course I love you.

30:11.820 --> 30:15.643
But my heart can't be
in two places at once.

30:17.459 --> 30:19.459
It's over.

30:19.461 --> 30:22.329
[Voice breaking] You need to
stop fighting for me.

30:24.165 --> 30:26.800
I'll stop fighting.

30:28.703 --> 30:31.471
As soon as we're back together.

30:31.473 --> 30:32.773
[Sighs]

30:32.775 --> 30:35.175
[Footsteps departing]

30:35.177 --> 30:36.944
Are you out of your mind?

30:36.946 --> 30:38.545
You were just supposed to
look around.

30:38.547 --> 30:40.147
It wasn't my fault.

30:40.149 --> 30:42.049
It was that <i> idiota</i> Spence.
He started it.

30:42.051 --> 30:43.483
I don't care!

30:43.485 --> 30:45.218
You put the whole plan
in danger.

30:45.220 --> 30:47.821
You're just worried your wife
will figure you out.

30:47.823 --> 30:49.823
I can cover it with Rosie,
okay?

30:49.825 --> 30:52.392
But I don't want to tell <i> El Jefe</i>
we lost the girl.

30:52.394 --> 30:56.463
[Sniffs]

30:56.465 --> 31:00.067
Spence saw me taking pictures
in her room.

31:00.069 --> 31:03.704
You are the <i> idiota.</i>

31:03.706 --> 31:07.574
I can't believe I have to work
with a stupid thug like you.

31:07.576 --> 31:10.077
You want me
to take care of him?

31:10.079 --> 31:13.914
No.
You leave Spence alone.

31:13.916 --> 31:15.449
I'll handle it.

31:17.685 --> 31:20.487
[Gunfire]
[Indistinct shouting]

31:22.557 --> 31:25.726
Deion, why don't you
get washed up for lunch?

31:25.728 --> 31:28.161
I'm talking to you, young man.

31:28.163 --> 31:29.396
[Up-tempo music playing]

31:29.398 --> 31:31.064
[Man grunts]

31:31.066 --> 31:32.199
Mother...

31:32.201 --> 31:34.668
[Boom!]

31:34.670 --> 31:38.572
Carmen, I need you
to punish Deion for me.

31:38.574 --> 31:41.875
I heard him cursing
at one of his video games.

31:41.877 --> 31:43.543
- Mrs. Powell...
- When I was a child,

31:43.545 --> 31:45.545
my mother would wash
my mouth out with soap.

31:45.547 --> 31:48.749
So, here's an artisanal
lemongrass body bar.

31:48.751 --> 31:50.751
- Huh?
- I want him to learn his lesson.

31:50.753 --> 31:52.753
But I see no reason
he shouldn't have the best.

31:52.755 --> 31:54.955
If you want Deion
to learn a lesson,

31:54.957 --> 31:56.456
it has to come from you.

31:56.458 --> 31:59.459
Oh! Oh, no.
No, I couldn't possibly.

31:59.461 --> 32:01.662
Because of Barrett?

32:03.197 --> 32:04.931
That's the reason, isn't it?

32:04.933 --> 32:07.968
♪

32:12.540 --> 32:16.943
The week before
Barrett was taken from us,

32:16.945 --> 32:21.370
he, uh... he broke
a very expensive vase.

32:22.151 --> 32:24.384
Now, I'd warned him not to
bounce balls in the house.

32:24.386 --> 32:27.320
But, like me, he was willful.

32:27.322 --> 32:32.092
And...
when the vase broke,

32:32.094 --> 32:34.294
I was furious.

32:35.997 --> 32:39.232
And I grounded him.

32:39.234 --> 32:42.586
And I told him
he was a very bad boy.

32:44.239 --> 32:46.719
[Voice breaking] And a few
days later, he was gone.

32:47.975 --> 32:52.412
Mrs. Powell, I am so sorry
about what happened.

32:52.414 --> 32:55.582
But Deion needs you to help him
become a good person.

32:58.252 --> 33:00.087
I am trying.

33:00.089 --> 33:03.690
But you can't just do
the fun part of parenting.

33:03.692 --> 33:05.258
You got to do it all.

33:07.929 --> 33:10.097
[Doorbell rings]

33:12.166 --> 33:14.367
Hi, there.
Can we talk?

33:14.369 --> 33:15.802
You sure you have time?

33:15.804 --> 33:17.270
I thought you were
on Death's door.

33:17.272 --> 33:19.873
Nope. Just yours.

33:19.875 --> 33:22.476
Please. I'd like the chance
to explain myself.

33:22.478 --> 33:26.480
Good. I actually have
some questions for you, too.

33:26.482 --> 33:28.315
Come on in.

33:30.017 --> 33:33.653
[Door close] So, kudos to
you for figuring me out.

33:33.655 --> 33:36.056
Yes. Faking cancer.

33:36.058 --> 33:39.192
I thought you were nuts before,
but somehow you topped yourself.

33:39.194 --> 33:40.627
I did, didn't I?

33:41.629 --> 33:45.732
But, sweetie, I'll be honest.
I thought we were friends.

33:45.734 --> 33:48.068
Did you really have to
tattle on me to Michael?

33:48.070 --> 33:50.203
I guess I did.

33:50.205 --> 33:53.039
[Sighs]
Well, it's really disappointing.

33:53.041 --> 33:55.375
I worked for months
on this plan.

33:55.377 --> 33:56.743
Plan?

33:56.745 --> 33:58.378
I had to break up
his marriage first,

33:58.380 --> 34:00.647
prove to Michael that
he was married to a whore.

34:00.649 --> 34:02.349
Excuse me?

34:02.351 --> 34:04.551
It was simple, really.

34:04.553 --> 34:07.821
I paid a man to approach Taylor,
sweet-talk her.

34:07.823 --> 34:10.322
You set Taylor up
to have an affair?

34:10.324 --> 34:12.159
That's right.

34:12.161 --> 34:14.761
And being the whore she is,
she took the bait.

34:14.763 --> 34:16.196
[Laughs]

34:16.197 --> 34:17.998
Who was she cheating with?

34:18.000 --> 34:21.400
I figured you'd want to know.

34:21.402 --> 34:24.237
I have his name in here
somewhere.

34:24.239 --> 34:25.405
Here it is.

34:25.407 --> 34:27.239
[Gasps]

34:27.242 --> 34:30.342
It's such a shame
when friendships have to end.

34:30.344 --> 34:31.745
♪

34:34.197 --> 34:36.565
Please, put the knife down.

34:36.567 --> 34:38.501
You just had to get involved,
didn't you?

34:38.503 --> 34:40.503
Is this why you killed Blanca?

34:40.505 --> 34:42.103
Because she found out
what you were up to?

34:42.106 --> 34:44.373
Blanca?
Michael's maid?

34:44.375 --> 34:45.841
You told me she was murdered.

34:45.842 --> 34:47.443
Michael's the one who thinks
she was murdered.

34:47.445 --> 34:49.045
I was just gossiping.

34:49.047 --> 34:50.679
So you didn't kill Blanca?

34:50.681 --> 34:52.581
No, but I am gonna kill you.

34:52.583 --> 34:54.984
Marisol! Aah!

34:55.886 --> 34:57.753
Jesse!
What are you doing here?

34:57.755 --> 34:59.855
Aah!
[Thud]

34:59.857 --> 35:01.290
Oh, my God. Jesse.

35:01.292 --> 35:02.525
Are you okay?

35:02.527 --> 35:04.960
You're the one who got stabbed.

35:04.962 --> 35:07.063
Jesse.

35:07.065 --> 35:08.297
Jesse!

35:08.299 --> 35:09.699
[Knock on door]

35:09.701 --> 35:11.701
I hope you don't mind
the interruption,

35:11.703 --> 35:15.037
but Deion has something
he would like to tell you.

35:16.306 --> 35:19.141
I'm sorry for messing
with your stuff

35:19.143 --> 35:22.545
and giving you a mustache
and shooting you in the butt.

35:22.547 --> 35:25.414
Well, it takes a good man
to admit he did something wrong.

35:25.416 --> 35:27.817
And I would have
laughed at the butt thing

35:27.819 --> 35:29.719
if it was somebody else's butt.

35:29.721 --> 35:32.088
[Chuckles]

35:36.326 --> 35:38.961
Okay, Deion.
Time to do homework.

35:38.963 --> 35:41.597
Okay.

35:42.933 --> 35:46.569
You know, in spite of your act,

35:46.571 --> 35:49.772
I think you have a place
in your heart for children.

35:52.409 --> 35:56.045
♪

36:21.505 --> 36:24.673
Here is your paycheck.

36:24.675 --> 36:28.878
With a little something extra,
as promised.

36:28.880 --> 36:30.880
I don't understand
why you wanted

36:30.882 --> 36:33.182
Zoila to think you were broke.

36:33.184 --> 36:34.216
You will.

36:38.188 --> 36:40.022
Zoila.

36:40.024 --> 36:41.857
We need to talk.

36:41.859 --> 36:44.493
These are not my cravings.
They're hers.

36:44.495 --> 36:46.328
And she does not know
what carbs are yet

36:46.330 --> 36:49.198
because she's a fetus.

36:51.501 --> 36:53.903
I spoke with Christopher.

36:53.905 --> 36:55.738
And I'm sure you'd agree,

36:55.740 --> 36:57.673
this year has been
very difficult for us.

36:57.675 --> 37:00.509
Oh, no.
You two broke up.

37:00.511 --> 37:03.913
I am so sorry, sweetie,
but maybe it is for the best.

37:03.915 --> 37:08.551
No. I'm talking about the
difficulties between you and me.

37:08.553 --> 37:11.754
I'm not sure I understand.

37:11.756 --> 37:16.725
Please promise me we'll always
be in each other's lives.

37:16.727 --> 37:19.087
Of course.
Why wouldn't we?

37:20.363 --> 37:24.567
I love you, Zoila.

37:24.569 --> 37:28.204
But I'm afraid I'm going to
have to let you go.

37:28.206 --> 37:31.507
♪

37:33.276 --> 37:34.710
How's the patient?

37:34.712 --> 37:36.111
All stitched up.

37:36.113 --> 37:37.780
They... they say
I'm gonna make it.

37:37.782 --> 37:40.783
Thank you again
for coming to my rescue.

37:40.785 --> 37:43.018
How did you know Olivia
was coming after me?

37:43.020 --> 37:45.855
Uh, she was pretty upset after
she talked to Mr. Stappord,

37:45.857 --> 37:48.217
so I decided to follow her.

37:49.226 --> 37:51.060
Well, the police took her
into custody,

37:51.062 --> 37:52.928
and she's under
a psych evaluation.

37:52.930 --> 37:56.131
I'm gonna go out on a limb
and say she cray.

37:56.133 --> 37:58.968
[Chuckles]
[Chuckles]

37:58.970 --> 38:02.404
But on the bright side,
you've got a sexy scar,

38:02.406 --> 38:05.407
and a great story to tell
at parties, right?

38:05.409 --> 38:06.909
More than one.

38:06.911 --> 38:09.745
Since I got here,
I've found a chopped-off hand,

38:09.747 --> 38:12.715
been stabbed,
held at gunpoint...

38:12.717 --> 38:14.783
Again,
I am so sorry about that.

38:14.785 --> 38:16.986
You know, I spent
three tours in Afghanistan,

38:16.988 --> 38:18.587
and I didn't see
this much action.

38:18.589 --> 38:20.709
[Laughs]
It has been kind of hectic, huh?

38:22.425 --> 38:26.061
Listen, Marisol,
when I met you,

38:26.063 --> 38:30.266
I told you I was looking
for peace and quiet.

38:30.268 --> 38:32.468
I don't think
I'm gonna find that here.

38:32.470 --> 38:34.837
[Sighs]

38:34.839 --> 38:37.940
So, what are you gonna do?

38:37.942 --> 38:40.342
I'm gonna go home to Seattle.

38:40.344 --> 38:42.778
It's where my sisters live.

38:42.780 --> 38:44.713
It'll be nice
to be around family.

38:47.584 --> 38:51.420
I'm sorry to hear that.

38:51.422 --> 38:52.821
I'm gonna miss you.

38:52.823 --> 38:55.257
Well, maybe I'll come back
and visit.

38:55.259 --> 38:58.093
Sure, if you ever need
a place to stay...

38:58.095 --> 38:59.695
Or a gun in your face.

38:59.697 --> 39:02.131
[Both laugh]

39:02.133 --> 39:03.732
I'll know who to call.

39:05.502 --> 39:06.583
[Sighs]

39:09.339 --> 39:11.739
I really hope you find
what you're looking for, Jesse.

39:13.043 --> 39:15.477
I hope you do, too.

39:15.479 --> 39:16.779
♪

39:23.853 --> 39:25.287
Poor Miguel.

39:25.289 --> 39:26.522
Are you kidding?

39:26.524 --> 39:29.558
Those kids saw
a real live fight.

39:29.560 --> 39:31.327
He'll be the star of his class.

39:31.329 --> 39:33.329
Still, I shouldn't have
invited Spence.

39:33.331 --> 39:35.531
I told him we need space.

39:35.533 --> 39:36.999
I'm glad to hear that.

39:37.001 --> 39:40.703
<i>Pero,</i> he did
say something strange.

39:40.705 --> 39:41.971
Oh?

39:41.973 --> 39:43.572
He said he caught that clown

39:43.574 --> 39:46.809
taking pictures of Katy's room.

39:46.811 --> 39:49.011
And I remember,
Mrs. Taylor said there were

39:49.013 --> 39:51.146
some bad people
looking for her.

39:51.148 --> 39:54.717
Come on, Rosita.
He was a clown.

39:54.719 --> 39:56.852
And you really think
there's nothing to worry about?

39:56.854 --> 39:59.688
I'll complain to the company
I hired him from.

39:59.690 --> 40:01.423
You'll never see him again.

40:01.425 --> 40:03.392
<i>Gracias, mi amor.</i>

40:03.394 --> 40:06.895
I'm so glad you're back,
Ernesto.

40:06.897 --> 40:11.333
Now let's clean this couch
so Mrs. Taylor doesn't fire me.

40:11.335 --> 40:13.168
Should I put this in the wash?

40:13.170 --> 40:16.372
Nope,
covers are dry-clean only,

40:16.374 --> 40:18.874
so we got to take them
to the...

40:18.876 --> 40:21.276
[Gasps]

40:21.278 --> 40:24.113
What is that?

40:24.115 --> 40:25.881
Looks like blood.

40:25.883 --> 40:27.383
Blood?

40:27.385 --> 40:29.718
Yeah, but someone tried
really hard to clean it up.

40:31.788 --> 40:33.422
Blanca.

40:33.424 --> 40:35.624
What?

40:35.626 --> 40:37.526
<i>Ay,</i> Ernesto.

40:37.528 --> 40:40.729
I think something terrible
happened in this room.

40:40.731 --> 40:43.732
♪

40:48.705 --> 40:50.539
[Knock on door]

40:50.541 --> 40:52.574
Who is it?

40:57.147 --> 40:58.580
[Sighs]
[Knocking continues]

40:58.582 --> 41:01.583
Yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

41:01.585 --> 41:02.584
<i>Hola, amigo.</i>

41:02.586 --> 41:04.153
Do I know you?

41:04.155 --> 41:07.022
It's me. Bobo.

41:08.291 --> 41:09.925
[Grunts]

41:09.927 --> 41:11.326
[Groans]

41:11.328 --> 41:14.864
♪

41:14.865 --> 41:17.039
<b>- sync and corrections by Zac -
- www.addic7ed.com -</b>

41:17.041 --> 41:19.508
The plan is on.
Tomorrow night we take the girl.

41:19.510 --> 41:20.910
<i>Next monday...</i>

41:20.912 --> 41:22.584
[Door opens]
What was that?

41:22.586 --> 41:24.225
Oh. I didn't hear anything.

41:24.227 --> 41:27.245
<i>With only one episode left
until the Season Finale...</i>

41:27.247 --> 41:30.576
You let him in, didn't you?
Stop lying to me!

41:30.578 --> 41:33.188
<i>They are coming dangerously
close to the truth.</i>

41:33.511 --> 41:34.401
[Groans]

41:35.244 --> 41:37.323
- [Screaming] Help me!
- What did you do?

41:37.804 --> 41:39.498
[Groans]

41:39.500 --> 41:41.173
<i>Maid for mondays...</i>

41:41.208 --> 41:44.511
<i>Devious Maids.
All new next Monday at 9.</i>

